    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="674"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1401.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to the embassy’s note of the 8th
                    instant, regarding the receipt of ammunition at Ojinaga by Gen. Luque, I have
                    the honor to inclose for your information and consideration a copy of a letter
                    from the Assistant Attorney General,<note n="1" xml:id="d674fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> stating that the matter will be given attention and
                    suggesting that his department be advised in advance of future shipments of the
                    kind mentioned.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
